  "body": "### What is wrong?\r\n\r\nChain re-orgs happen and it would be nice to see some info about them when running trinity.\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed\r\n\r\nWhenever trinity is syncing and it encounters a chain reorg we should log something with depth and hashes.  Probably configurable to a certain minimum depth.\r\n\r\nFor lightchain, this should be relatively easy.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/py-evm/blob/master/p2p/lightchain.py#L214\r\n\r\nAnywhere that `headerdb.coro_persist_header` is called should return an iterable of headers which are *new* to the canonical chain.  If the returned list contains more than 1 entry then the chain just re-organized.\r\n\r\nDoing this for full sync is going to require updates to the Py-EVM API so that `chain.import_block` returns an iterable of blocks that are part of the new canonical chain.",
